==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|gnagan|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|gnaganan|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|knagen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|nagen|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|gnaga|lang=sv}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/nɔː/}}
* {{audio|en-us-gnaw.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɔː}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|gnaws|gnawing|gnawed|'''[[gnawed]]''' or '''[[gnawn]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To [[bite]] something persistently.
#: ''Her teeth '''gnawed''' at me all night, keeping me twisting and turning from pain.''
#: ''We saw that the dog had been '''gnawing''' on the bone.''
# {{intransitive}} To produce excessive anxiety or worry.
#: ''Her comment '''gnawed''' at me all night, keeping me twisting and turning in bed.''

